CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, May 10, 1958, pg. A1, reads: "Detective to Retire - J. Voyle Parker, full-fledged member of the City Detective Bureau for the past 21 years, will retire on June 1. He is shown with his wife, Madelyn Parker, the oldest in period of service Democratic committeewoman of the Fifth Ward. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Detective J. Voyle Parker holding document, and his wife Madelyn Parker, in their home at 446 Morgan Street, vertical format
